{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/blog/adm-application-descriptor-manager/","webpackCompilationHash":"a5b98ff0be163133161f","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"James Ford","author":"James Ford"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"cdfd4844-72c6-58a6-8c7c-36d58ba08cce","html":"<p><a href=\"http://www.dehats.com/drupal/?q=node/55\"><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 500px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 55.99999999999999%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"adm\"\n        title=\"adm\"\n        src=\"/static/4a65309fec4c9b0753b84031c39556de/48a11/adm.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4a65309fec4c9b0753b84031c39556de/afcd2/adm.jpg 300w,\n/static/4a65309fec4c9b0753b84031c39556de/48a11/adm.jpg 500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\"\n      />\n    </span></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.dehats.com/drupal/?q=node/55\">Application Descriptior Manager</a> is another application like the <a href=\"http://www.gskinner.com/blog/archives/2008/09/beware_the_air.html\">AIR Badger</a> and <a href=\"http://clockmaker.jp/labs/air_icon/\">Icon Generator</a> - a development tool, built in AIR, for developing AIR applications.  It's useful, functional and has reassuring touches like auto-backup, or version upgrade buttons.</p>\n<p>Once installed, you point it at an AIR application descriptor file, which it reads in, and displays the contents in a few simple flex forms.  Of course, editing the XML yourself isn't something that's out of the question normally, but the ADM application makes it all easier to manage - just like the AIR Badger does for the application install badges.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.dehats.com/drupal/?q=node/55\">Download the ADM application from Flex My Day.</a></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"ADM - Application Descriptor Manager","date":"December 02, 2008","tags":["adobe-air"],"url":null,"image":null,"description":null,"image_credit":null}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"prev":{"frontmatter":{"path":"/blog/getting-your-source-code-hosted-on-google-code/","tags":["actionscript","air","applicationinfo","google-code","subversion"],"title":"Getting your source code hosted on Google Code...","date":"2008-12-01T17:00:58.000Z","description":null,"image":null}},"next":{"frontmatter":{"path":"/blog/resize-multiple-images-and-package-them-for-e-mail-transmission-introducing-imagesizer/","tags":["imagesizer","air","fzip"],"title":"Resize multiple images and package them for e-mail transmission - introducing ImageSizer!","date":"2008-12-02T11:45:30.000Z","description":null,"image":null}}}}}